Details

A qualified noun phrase can be either singular or plural. The number is a feature of the overall phrase; the phrase might consist of subphrases of different numbers (for example, "bob's coins" is plural even though it contains a singular subphrase, "bob"; and "one of the coins" is singular, even though its subphrase "coins" is plural). `grammar `[`qualifiedNounPhrase`](../object/qualifiedNounPhrase.html)`(main)`` :   `[`LayeredNounPhraseProd`](../object/LayeredNounPhraseProd.html)
